<section xml:id="_a_bored_circular_cross_section">
<title>A bored circular cross-section</title>
<note>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem>
<simpara>A <inlineequation><alt><![CDATA[30 mm]]></alt><mathphrase><![CDATA[30 mm]]></mathphrase></inlineequation> diameter bar is subjected to an axial tensile load of <inlineequation><alt><![CDATA[115 kN]]></alt><mathphrase><![CDATA[115 kN]]></mathphrase></inlineequation>. Under the action of this load a <inlineequation><alt><![CDATA[200 mm]]></alt><mathphrase><![CDATA[200 mm]]></mathphrase></inlineequation> gauge length is found to extend <inlineequation><alt><![CDATA[0.15 \times 10^{-3} mm]]></alt><mathphrase><![CDATA[0.15 \times 10^{-3} mm]]></mathphrase></inlineequation>. Determine the modulus of elasticity for the bar material.</simpara>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<simpara>To reduce weight whilst keeping the external diameter constant, the bar is bored axially to produce a cylinder of uniform thickness, what is the maximum diameter of bore possible given that the maximum allowable stress is <inlineequation><alt><![CDATA[245 MN/m^2]]></alt><mathphrase><![CDATA[245 MN/m^2]]></mathphrase></inlineequation>? The load can be assumed to remain constant at <inlineequation><alt><![CDATA[115 kN]]></alt><mathphrase><![CDATA[115 kN]]></mathphrase></inlineequation>.</simpara>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<simpara>What will be the change in the outside diameter of the bar under the limiting stress quoted above? (<inlineequation><alt><![CDATA[E = 210 GN/m^2]]></alt><mathphrase><![CDATA[E = 210 GN/m^2]]></mathphrase></inlineequation> and <inlineequation><alt><![CDATA[v = 0.3]]></alt><mathphrase><![CDATA[v = 0.3]]></mathphrase></inlineequation>)</simpara>
</listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</note>
<informalexample>
<simpara><inlinemediaobject><?asciidoc-br?>
<imageobject><?asciidoc-br?>
<imagedata fileref="./images/icons/key.png"/><?asciidoc-br?>
</imageobject><?asciidoc-br?>
<textobject><phrase>key</phrase></textobject><?asciidoc-br?>
</inlinemediaobject> <emphasis>modulus of elasticity</emphasis><?asciidoc-br?>
<inlineequation><alt><![CDATA[\frac{\sigma}{\epsilon} = E]]></alt><mathphrase><![CDATA[\frac{\sigma}{\epsilon} = E]]></mathphrase></inlineequation><?asciidoc-br?>
<inlineequation><alt><![CDATA[\epsilon = \frac{\Delta L}{L}]]></alt><mathphrase><![CDATA[\epsilon = \frac{\Delta L}{L}]]></mathphrase></inlineequation><?asciidoc-br?>
<inlineequation><alt><![CDATA[E = \sigma \frac{L}{\Delta L}]]></alt><mathphrase><![CDATA[E = \sigma \frac{L}{\Delta L}]]></mathphrase></inlineequation><?asciidoc-br?>
<inlineequation><alt><![CDATA[E = \frac{F}{A} \times \frac{L}{\Delta L}]]></alt><mathphrase><![CDATA[E = \frac{F}{A} \times \frac{L}{\Delta L}]]></mathphrase></inlineequation><?asciidoc-br?>
<inlineequation><alt><![CDATA[E = \frac{F}{\pi \times \big(\frac{D}{2}\big)^2} \times \frac{L}{\Delta L}]]></alt><mathphrase><![CDATA[E = \frac{F}{\pi \times \big(\frac{D}{2}\big)^2} \times \frac{L}{\Delta L}]]></mathphrase></inlineequation></simpara>
