<chapter xml:id="_compound_bars">
<title>Compound Bars</title>
<section xml:id="_theory_2">
<title>Theory</title>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem>
<simpara>A compound or composite bar consists of one or more materials bonded together rigidly such that the straining action of the external load is shared by the materials such that they satisfy <emphasis role="strong">equilibrium condition</emphasis>, <inlineequation><alt><![CDATA[F_{s} + F_{c} = F_{total}]]></alt><mathphrase><![CDATA[F_{s} + F_{c} = F_{total}]]></mathphrase></inlineequation>.</simpara>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<simpara>These different materials are constrained to deform together such that they satisfy <emphasis role="strong">compatibility condition</emphasis>, <inlineequation><alt><![CDATA[\epsilon_{material1} = \epsilon_{material2}]]></alt><mathphrase><![CDATA[\epsilon_{material1} = \epsilon_{material2}]]></mathphrase></inlineequation>.</simpara>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<simpara><emphasis role="strong">Modular ratio</emphasis>, <inlineequation><alt><![CDATA[m]]></alt><mathphrase><![CDATA[m]]></mathphrase></inlineequation>, is given by <inlineequation><alt><![CDATA[\frac{E_{material1}}{E_{material2}}]]></alt><mathphrase><![CDATA[\frac{E_{material1}}{E_{material2}}]]></mathphrase></inlineequation>.</simpara>
</listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</section>
<section xml:id="_examples_2">
<title>Examples</title>
<section xml:id="_a_concrete_column_with_steel_reinforcement">
<title>A concrete column with steel reinforcement</title>
<note>
<simpara>A reinforced cement concrete column of dimension <inlineequation><alt><![CDATA[625\ mm \times 625\ mm]]></alt><mathphrase><![CDATA[625\ mm \times 625\ mm]]></mathphrase></inlineequation> has eight steel rods of diameter <inlineequation><alt><![CDATA[30\ mm]]></alt><mathphrase><![CDATA[30\ mm]]></mathphrase></inlineequation> as reinforcement. Find the stresses in steel and concrete, and the elastic shortening of the column if <inlineequation><alt><![CDATA[E =\ 200,000\ N/mm^2]]></alt><mathphrase><![CDATA[E =\ 200,000\ N/mm^2]]></mathphrase></inlineequation> for steel and <inlineequation><alt><![CDATA[10,000\ N/mm^2]]></alt><mathphrase><![CDATA[10,000\ N/mm^2]]></mathphrase></inlineequation> for concrete. Load on column <inlineequation><alt><![CDATA[=\ 3000\ kN]]></alt><mathphrase><![CDATA[=\ 3000\ kN]]></mathphrase></inlineequation> and length <inlineequation><alt><![CDATA[=\ 4\ m]]></alt><mathphrase><![CDATA[=\ 4\ m]]></mathphrase></inlineequation>.</simpara>
</note>
